					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">With a vblank bandwidth like that, I wish more Master System games would animate background patterns to create richer visuals... But most games stick to updating only the player's patterns. Some SMS games have really good background art when compared to the NES, because of the huge advantage of 4bpp tiles, but they tend to be mostly static, which kills the mood a bit. NES games with CHR-RAM also rarely animate backgrounds, but many CHR-ROM games do it, and it makes them look more advanced. If more SMS games had such animations, some could even pass for 16-bit titles.</div>

