						<div class="postbody">Effects that the NES can do as well. <em>MetalStorm</em> is an exercise in dynamic tile basturmation, and later NES games like <em>Vice: Project Doom</em>, <em>Bucky O'Hare</em>, and <em>The Curse of Possum Hollow</em> show off hsync scrolls. The one thing PCE has over NES and SMS in this sense is more sprite overdraw.</div>

